      • taskFinished

        @HTTPServiceMethod(name="taskFinished",
                   acceptedMethods="POST")
public void taskFinished(@HTTPAuthenticationParameter(required=false)
                                                                                                              core.tut.pori.http.parameters.AuthenticationParameter authenticatedUser,
                                                                                                              @HTTPMethodParameter(name="body",bodyParameter=true)
                                                                                                              core.tut.pori.http.parameters.InputStreamParameter xml)
        The request is to be sent in the body of POST method. The Content-Type header MUST be set to "text/xml". The character set MUST be UTF-8. For example, "Content-Type: text/xml; charset=UTF-8". The method can be called multiple times by the back-ends. Each call is assumed to be an incremental update on the previous one and can contain any amount of new information.

        Example Query:

        POST /rest/csers/"taskFinished"
        Content-Type: text/xml; charset=UTF-8

        [HTTP BODY STARTS]
        <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<task>
  <dataVisibility>PRIVATE</dataVisibility>
  <taskIdList>
    <taskId>5e4f7207-8f50-4ac7-9a0a-e207d4bdf529</taskId>
  </taskIdList>
  <taskTypeList>
    <taskType>gather</taskType>
  </taskTypeList>
  <backendList>
    <backend>
      <backendId>5740505185497538396</backendId>
      <message>glxqxtydickjwcssefainnppuotpjmbszddaismhferxcilgjrjvrapjzqsxvyay</message>
      <taskStatus>UNKNOWN</taskStatus>
    </backend>
  </backendList>
  <callbackUri>http://example.org:8080/ApiltaService/rest/sensors/taskFinished</callbackUri>
  <measurementList>
    <measurement>
      <backendId>5740505185497538396</backendId>
      <measurementId>d9580922-4994-42be-8e59-f8773d6535b5</measurementId>
    </measurement>
  </measurementList>
</task>

        [HTTP BODY ENDS]

        Example Result:

        <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<response method="taskFinished" service="csers">
  <status>OK</status>
</response>
        Parameters:
        authenticatedUser -
        xml - Only the result data should be in the body. See SensorTask

      • queryTaskDetails

        @HTTPServiceMethod(name="queryTaskDetails",
                   acceptedMethods="GET")
public core.tut.pori.http.Response queryTaskDetails(@HTTPAuthenticationParameter(required=false)
                                                                                                                                            core.tut.pori.http.parameters.AuthenticationParameter authenticatedUser,
                                                                                                                                            @HTTPMethodParameter(name="backend_id")
                                                                                                                                            core.tut.pori.http.parameters.LongParameter backendId,
                                                                                                                                            @HTTPMethodParameter(name="task_id")
                                                                                                                                            core.tut.pori.http.parameters.LongParameter taskId,
                                                                                                                                            @HTTPMethodParameter(name="data_groups",required=false)
                                                                                                                                            core.tut.pori.http.parameters.DataGroups dataGroups,
                                                                                                                                            @HTTPMethodParameter(name="limits",required=false)
                                                                                                                                            core.tut.pori.http.parameters.Limits limits)
        This method can be used to retrieve the up-to-date details and progress of a previously scheduled task.

        Example Query:

        GET /rest/csers/"queryTaskDetails"?"backend_id"=1&"task_id"=1

        Example Result:

        <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<response method="queryTaskDetails" service="csers">
  <task>
    <createdTimestamp>2018-06-05T21:33:50Z</createdTimestamp>
    <description>bkgjfeeevsmytxidnuhredjueivgmudkuppbwyueerhcbemwtitlngpcugyxooqi</description>
    <dataVisibility>PUBLIC</dataVisibility>
    <name>fskbtbkllasklpzcjgxnuloulhnjugqzuvobzytlrwcscrjvivcmlthjndlbassj</name>
    <taskState>ARCHIVED</taskState>
    <taskIdList>
      <taskId>0f251323-36b5-408c-8611-eef6ef22a337</taskId>
    </taskIdList>
    <taskTypeList>
      <taskType>gather</taskType>
    </taskTypeList>
    <updatedTimestamp>2019-05-31T05:36:40Z</updatedTimestamp>
    <userDetails>
      <userId>5303056864055389253</userId>
    </userDetails>
    <backendList>
      <backend>
        <backendId>1</backendId>
      </backend>
    </backendList>
    <callbackUri>http://example.org:8080/ApiltaService/rest/sensors/taskFinished</callbackUri>
    <when>
      <condition>
        <terms>
          <entry>
            <key>fcwaa</key>
            <value>wtmjojatty</value>
          </entry>
          <entry>
            <key>time/validFromToRange</key>
            <value>2017-09-21T23:50:16.970Z/2019-02-26T09:21:43.970Z</value>
          </entry>
        </terms>
      </condition>
    </when>
    <what>
      <output>
        <feature>sywxb</feature>
      </output>
    </what>
  </task>
  <status>OK</status>
</response>
        Parameters:
        authenticatedUser -
        taskId -
        backendId -
        dataGroups -
        limits - paging limits
        Returns:
        response See SensorTask

      • createFile

        @HTTPServiceMethod(name="createFile",
                   acceptedMethods="POST")
public core.tut.pori.http.Response createFile(@HTTPAuthenticationParameter(required=false)
                                                                                                                                 core.tut.pori.http.parameters.AuthenticationParameter authenticatedUser,
                                                                                                                                 @HTTPMethodParameter(name="backend_id")
                                                                                                                                 core.tut.pori.http.parameters.LongParameter backendId,
                                                                                                                                 @HTTPMethodParameter(name="body",bodyParameter=true)
                                                                                                                                 core.tut.pori.http.parameters.InputStreamParameter file)
        The request is to be sent in the body of POST method.

        Example Query:

        POST /rest/csers/createFile?"backend_id"=1
        Content-Type: text/xml; charset=UTF-8

        [HTTP BODY STARTS]
        [ANY FILE CONTENT]
        [HTTP BODY ENDS]

        Example Result:

        <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<response method="createFile" service="csers">
  <fileDetailsList>
    <fileDetails>
      <GUID>ab803aea-dff6-445c-95f2-fa6839dcd85a</GUID>
    </fileDetails>
  </fileDetailsList>
  <status>OK</status>
</response>
        Parameters:
        authenticatedUser -
        backendId -
        file - only the file contents should be in the body.
        Returns:
        FileDetailsList with identifier for the generated file
